24,"formats":{"large":{"ext":".png","url":"/uploads/large_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea.png","hash":"large_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea","mime":"image/png","name":"large_Mac 512@2x.png","path":null,"size":274.13,"width":1000,"height":1000},"small":{"ext":".png","url":"/uploads/small_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea.png","hash":"small_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea","mime":"image/png","name":"small_Mac 512@2x.png","path":null,"size":88.35,"width":500,"height":500},"medium":{"ext":".png","url":"/uploads/medium_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea.png","hash":"medium_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea","mime":"image/png","name":"medium_Mac 512@2x.png","path":null,"size":178.46,"width":750,"height":750},"thumbnail":{"ext":".png","url":"/uploads/thumbnail_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea.png","hash":"thumbnail_Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea","mime":"image/png","name":"thumbnail_Mac 512@2x.png","path":null,"size":18.21,"width":156,"height":156}},"hash":"Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea","ext":".png","mime":"image/png","size":47.48,"url":"/uploads/Mac_512_2x_14e7c839ea.png","previewUrl":null,"provider":"local","provider_metadata":null,"createdAt":"2022-06-01T18:09:12.886Z","updatedAt":"2022-06-01T18:09:12.886Z"}}}}}],"posts":[{"id":"629ba6886440ae0001667a3d","uuid":"2a1eb17d-fc21-4ecb-96b6-8fdf8e32f39e","title":"Observe UserDefaults with Combine","slug":"userdefaults-and-combine","html":"<p>Observing UserDefaults with a Combine publisher is quite simple and powerful.</p><p>Let’s assume that we want to observe the playback speed a user set inside the app.</p><p>The first thing we need to do is extend UserDefaults with a computed property for the playback speed.</p><pre><code class=\"language-swift\">extension UserDefaults {\n\t@objc dynamic var playbackSpeed: Float {\n\t\treturn float(forKey: \"playbackSpeed\")\n\t}\n}\n</code></pre><p>You can now observe the value for <code>playbackSpeed</code> where ever you want to. For example inside a view controller.</p><pre><code class=\"language-swift\">import UIKit\nimport Combine\n\nclass ViewController: UIViewController {\n\n\tprivate var subscriptions = Set&lt;AnyChancellable&gt;()\n\n\toverride func viewDidLoad() {\n\t\tsuper.viewDidLoad()\n\t\n\t\tUserDefaults.standard.publisher(for: \\.playbackSpeed)\n\t\t\t.sink { playbackSpeed in \n\t\t\t\tprint(\"The current playback speed is \\(playbackSpeed)\")\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t.store(in: &amp;subscriptions)\n\t}\n\n}\n</code></pre><p>Setting the value for <code>playbackSpeed</code> works as always.</p><pre><code class=\"language-swift\">UserDefaults.standard.set(1.25, forKey: \"playbackSpeed\")\n</code></pre><h2 id=\"swiftui\">SwiftUI</h2><p>By the way, SwiftUI observes UserDefaults out of the box using <code>@AppStorage</code>.</p><pre><code class=\"language-swift\">import SwiftUI\n\nstruct MyView: View {\n\t@AppStorage(\"playbackSpeed\") var playbackSpeed: Float = 1.0\n\n\tvar body: some View {\n        Slider(value: $playbackSpeed, in: 0.5...2.0)\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>","comment_id":"629ba6886440ae0001667a3d","feature_image":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1508739773434-c26b3d09e071?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=MnwxMTc3M3wwfDF8c2VhcmNofDZ8fG1hY3xlbnwwfHx8fDE2NTQ0MzI0MDQ&ixlib=rb-1.2.1&q=80&w=2000","featured":false,"visibility":"public","created_at":"2022-06-04T18:38:00.000+00:00","updated_at":"2022-06-06T16:20:54.000+00:00","published_at":"2022-06-05T17:00:00.000+00:00","custom_excerpt":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_foot":null,"custom_template":null,"canonical_url":"https://swiftbytimo.com/posts/userdefaults-combine","tags":[{"id":"629c7b976440ae0001667a53","name":"Combine","slug":"combine","description":null,"feature_image":null,"visibility":"public","og_image":null,"og_title":null,"og_description":null,"twitter_image":null,"twitter_title":null,"twitter_description":null,"meta_title":null,"meta_description":null,"codeinjection_head":null,"codeinjection_foot":null,"canonical_url":null,"accent_color":null,"url":"https://cms-swiftbytimo.nxtaws.com/tag/combine/"}],"primary_tag":{"id":"629c7b976440ae00016